        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Gnish</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Thats the name!</P><P>Wizened Herb Collector was the unmezzable one.  When looking at the front door, he is off to the left and behind the building in a tunnel, but easily viewable.</P><P>As for pulling, this is how I did it.</P><P>Level 57 warrior (me).  I used distance aggro for the most part.  Walk up til you get aggro then run back to the group.  I did bow shoot the Wizened guy though and had 2 from the house dump into my pull, so we had 3 (house was a PH).</P><P>We were one group with 59 enc.  I don't recall any bad pulls happening after we pulled the house, but we did have spawns or chain aggro somewhere as we had adds coming to us for a little bit, before they finally stopped.</P><P>As for getting there, I think the easiest way is (take this with a grain of salt mind you).</P><P>- Fight down to the first bridge.  DMF up.  Drop down there.  Fight that stuff (1-2).  <BR>- Take a right and fight that path (get the Captain and Bridge Keeper if up, otherwise just walk by them - by walking past, I mean don't turn right into their corridor, just keep on going straight the way you were).  <BR>- Once you come to the T, choose the path going down (left).  Follow that all the way to the next crossroad.<BR>- Take a right<BR>- After that you should run right into the herbie, but I'm not 100% sure.  We usually go left and hit the treasury instead, but I am told that right takes you to the herbalist.</P><P>A FD puller is great, but really, a warrior could do most of it.  Up to that point, 1 pull of 4 was possible, but the rest was 1-2 pulls.</P><P>I hope this helps.</P><P>/salute</P><P> </font></td>
